 4b69f2ce-0e87-4176-8915-f39c40f7e16d.732390b1-b938-438d-ac4a-a06e19645c7d.description=Description\: 

This step creates a setting file that includes the install options for the list of application archive files being deployed by the application server.

Return Code\:
0 \= Step ran successfully
1 \= Step failed.



Inputs\:
 command - executes CreateInstallOptionsFileforApplicationArchives.py
 Application Archive File List - Required\: Comma-separated list of the Application Archive files to be deployed. Example\: xxx.war or yyy.ear
 Archive Install Option All Server Groups - Optional\: Specifies whether the product examines the application references specified during application installation or updating and, if validation is enabled, warns you of incorrect references or fails the operation. The possible values are off, warn and fail. Specify off for no resource validation, warn for warning messages about incorrect resource references, or fail to stop operations that fail as a result of incorrect resource references.
 Archive Install Option Allow dispatching includes to remote resources - Optional\: Specifies whether or not an application can dispatch Include operations to resources across web modules located in different Java virtual machines in a managed node environment using the standard request dispatcher mechanism. Possible values are Yes or No.
 Archive Install Option Allow servicing includes from remote resources - Optional\: Specifies whether or not an enterprise application can service an Include request from an application. Possible values are Yes or No.
 Archive Install Option Application Build ID - Optional\: Specifies an uneditable string that identifies the Build ID version of the application.
 Archive Install Option Asynchronous Request Dispatch Type - Optional\: Specifies whether or not web modules can dispatch requests concurrently on separate threads and, if so, whether the server or client dispatches the requests. Concurrent dispatching can improve servlet response time.
 Archive Install Option Business level application name - Optional\: Specifies that either the product creates a new business-level application name with the enterprise application that you are installing, or, makes the enterprise application a composition unit of an existing business-level application.
 Archive Install Option Create MBeans for resources - Optional\: Specifies whether or not to create MBeans for resources such as servlets or JSP files within an application when the application starts. The default behavior is to create MBeans. Possible values are Yes or No.
 Archive Install Option Deploy enterprise beans - Optional\: Specifies whether or not the EJBDeploy tool runs during application installation. Possible values are Yes or No.
 Archive Install Option Distribute application - Optional\: Specifies whether or not the product expands application binaries in the installation location during installation and deletes application binaries during uninstallation. The default is to enable application distribution. Application binaries for installed applications are expanded to the directory specified. Possible values are Yes or No.
 Archive Install Option File Permission - Optional\: Specifies access permissions for application binaries for installed applications that are expanded to the specified directory. Possible values are\: *\=755 or .*\.dll\=755\#.*\.so\=755\#.*\.a\=755\#.*\.sl\=755 or .*\.htm\=755\#.*\.html\=755\#.*\.gif\=755\#.*\.jpg\=755
 Archive Install Option Force Deploy - Optional\: Specifies whether the product examines the application references specified during application installation or updating and, if validation is enabled, warns you of incorrect references or fails the operation. The possible values are off, warn and fail. Specify off for no resource validation, warn for warning messages about incorrect resource references, or fail to stop operations that fail as a result of incorrect resource references.
 Archive Install Option Override class reloading settings for Web and EJB modules - Optional\: Specifies whether or not the product run time detects changes to application classes when the application is running. If enabled, and application classes are changed, then the application is stopped and restarted to reload updated classes. Possible values are Yes or No.
 Archive Install Option Precompile JavaServer Pages files - Optional\: Specifies whether or not to precompile JavaServer Pages (JSP) files as a part of installation. The default is not to precompile JSP files. Possible values are Yes or No.
 Archive Install Option Process embedded configuration - Optional\: Specifies whether or not the embedded configuration should be processed. An embedded configuration consists of files such as resource.xml, variables.xml, and deployment.xml. You can collect WebSphere Application Server-specific deployment information and store it in the application EAR file. You can then install the EAR file into a WebSphere Application Server configuration using application management interfaces. Possible values are Yes or No.
 Archive Install Option Reload interval in seconds - Optional\: Specifies the number of seconds to scan the application's file system for updated files. The default is the value of the reloading interval attribute in the IBM extension (META-INF/ibm-application-ext.xmi) file of the EAR file. The reloading interval attribute takes effect only if class reloading is enabled. To enable reloading, specify a value greater than zero (for example, 1 to 2147483647). To disable reloading, specify zero (0). The range is from 0 to 2147483647.
 Archive Install Option Runtime Name - Optional\: Specifies whether the product examines the application references specified during application installation or updating and, if validation is enabled, warns you of incorrect references or fails the operation. The possible values are off, warn and fail. Specify off for no resource validation, warn for warning messages about incorrect resource references, or fail to stop operations that fail as a result of incorrect resource references.
 Archive Install Option Server Groups - Optional\: Specifies whether the product examines the application references specified during application installation or updating and, if validation is enabled, warns you of incorrect references or fails the operation. The possible values are off, warn and fail. Specify off for no resource validation, warn for warning messages about incorrect resource references, or fail to stop operations that fail as a result of incorrect resource references.
 Archive Install Option Use Binary Configuration - Optional\: Specifies whether or not the application server uses the binding, extensions, and deployment descriptors located with the application deployment document, the deployment.xml file (default), or those located in the enterprise archive (EAR) file. Select this setting for applications installed on Version 6.0 or later deployment targets only. Possible values are Yes or No.
 Archive Install Option Validate Install - Optional\: Specifies whether or not the product examines the application references specified during application installation or updating and, if validation is enabled, warns users about incorrect references or fails the operation. Possible values are Off, Warn and Fail. Specify Off for no resource validation, Warn for warning messages about incorrect resource references, or Fail to stop operations that fail as a result of incorrect resource references.
 Archive Setting File - Optional\: The file containing the install options for all the archive files to be deployed.
 Code Release History Location - Required\: Fully qualified path name of the location where the application archive will be saved (for history purposes) on the target machine. This location cannot be the same as the Code Release Staging Location.
 Code Release Staging Location - Required\: Fully qualified path name of the location where the application archive will be saved on the target machine. This location cannot be the same as the Code Release History Location.
 Install Options for Middleware - Required\: This is a flag to set for which middleware the install options going to set.
 host - Target to run this command against
 password - Login information for host
 username - Login information for host
 protocol - ssh/wmi
 timeout - Time (ms) before auto-exit\: use ${ExtendedTimeout} to lengthen.

Results\:
 Exit Code - Exit code of the step needed for branching.

 4b69f2ce-0e87-4176-8915-f39c40f7e16d.description=<pre>
 Purpose

This workflow automates application deployments in Oracle WebLogic Server. In addition to deployment automation, this workflow can update JVM Generic Arguments and JVM System Properties on the Web Server, and also provides install options for application deployments.

Some install options are provided as parameters for the workflow, or, users can specify install options within a file for each of the applications to be deployed (Note that user-specified parameter values take the highest precedence). This workflow provides application deployment verification by providing the URLs. For successful application deployments, verifications and a list of the applications are maintained in the history file. In cases of unsuccessful application deployments, the workflow rolls back the deployment and restores the last successfully deployed application (if any).

The supported applications are of type \:
 - .war files
 - .ear files


 Required Inputs

 Server Target - The desired target to run this flow against.
 Server Target Username - The user to login to the Server Target as.
 Server Target Password - The password to login as the Server Target Username.
 Download Source Host - The target host where the files needed for this flow can be downloaded from.
 Download Source Path - The path to where the files can be found on the Download Source Host.
 Admin Password - Required\: The Administrator password for logging into the WebLogic Server.
 Admin Server Hostname - Required\: The Admin Server Hostname.
 Admin Server Port - Required\: The port number of the Admin WebLogic Server
 Admin Username - Required\: The Admin Username for logging into the WebLogic Server.
 Application Archive File List - Required\: Comma separated list of Application Archives to be deployed.
 BEA Home - Required\: Fully qualified path to the product installation directory in which to install WebLogic Server. For instance /opt/oracle/WebLogic.
 Code Release History Location - Required\: Fully qualified path name of the location where the application archive will be saved (for history purposes) on the target machine. This location cannot be the same as the Code Release Staging Location.
 Code Release Staging Location - Required\: Fully qualified path name of the location where the application archive will be saved on the target machine. This location cannot be the same as the Code Release History Location.
 Md5 Checksum - Required\: Comma-separated list of the MD5 Checksum of the Application Archive files to be deployed.
Please provide the Checksum for the Archive File if listed.
 Server.Become User - No description
 Test URLs - Required\: Comma-separated list of URLs used to test whether or not the list of applications deployed successfully. Example\: http\://mytestdb.com, http\://yourtest.com
 WLS Install Home - Required\: Fully qualified path to the Middleware Home directory that will contain this installation. For instance /opt/oracle/WebLogic/wlserver_10.3

 Optional Inputs

 Clean Code Base - Remove code base from target after execution (True || False).
 Clean JRE - Remove JRE from target after execution (True || False).
 Download From SA - Download binaries from SA (True || False). Must set override for 'SAUser' System Account.
 SA Folder Path - Location of binaries on SA. Must set override for 'SAUser' System Account.
 Debug Level - Set level of output [(least) 1-5 (most)]
 JVM System Properties - Optional\: Specifies the JVM System Properties. Provide string in the following format\: -DPropertyName\=PropertyValue
 Domain Path - Optional\: Fully qualified path of the domain under which the Admin server resides.
Ex\: /opt/oracle/weblogic/user_projects/domains/mydomain_name/
 JVM Memory Arguments - Optional\: Specifies the JVM memory arguments. Provide values as standard JVM settings with space as delimiter.
Ex\: -Xms256m -Xmx512m
 Cleanup on Failure - Optional\: Determines whether or not to remove downloaded and extracted files. This parameter also cleans up the installed directory upon failure of the workflow.
 Cleanup on Success - Optional\: Determines whether or not to remove downloaded and extracted files. This parameter also cleans up the installed directory upon successful execution of the workflow.
 Archive Setting File - Optional\: The file containing the install options for all the archive file.

 Dependencies

This workflow requires\:
 - A working WebLogic Application Server on a standalone setup (Provisioning the WebLogic Software and Creating the Domain and Admin Server.)
 - You must run the Discover WebLogic workflow before you run this workflow. The Discover WebLogic workflow audits the server's physical environment for WebLogic cells, clusters, and application servers and then stores the configuration information in the HP DMA environment.

 Results Verification

The Console will indicate whether the workflow completed without errors. The workflow results will indicate whether the create was successful.



 Additional Documentation

The HP Database and Middleware Automation Support Matrix is available in the HP Software product manuals library located here\: 

"http\://h20230.www2.hp.com/selfsolve/manuals"\:http\://h20230.www2.hp.com/selfsolve/manuals

In the Product box, select Database and Middleware Automation Solution Packs. Specify the version of HP DMA that you have, and select any operating system that is listed. Click Search to view a list of pertinent documents.
</pre> 4b69f2ce-0e87-4176-8915-f39c40f7e16d.eace3e86-9e8d-446b-9dc6-3d9281d57b59.description=Purpose\:
